So, in a URL< a question mark indicates the end of the location. Once we end the location we're actually passing parameters into the URL. Parameters are separated by &

So here, we actually have a callback, a format, and text. 

Callback= is a parameter that tells the server what javascript function to call. 

So in this scenario, we would have written a function called received.

